<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Joe Biden called for gun control, less than 24 hours after two LA County sheriff's deputies were shot in the head and wounded during an ambush in Compton.</p>

<p>'Weapons of war have no place in our communities,' the former Vice President tweeted. 'We need to ban assault weapons and high-capacity magazines.'</p>

<p>Despite calling the shooting 'unconscionable' earlier in the day and demanding justice, Biden's comments were in stark contrast to Trump's call for a 'fast trial' and the death penalty for the 'animal' who carried it out - should the officers die.</p>

